                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18430227-976-offence-1 t18430227-name-846"></join>Charles Fowler</persName> and another.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-847" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-847" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-847" type="surname" value="PENNY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-847" type="given" value="ALFRED"></interp>ALFRED PENNY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am shopman to Mr. Charles Fowler and another, pawnbrokers, Old-street. On the 9th of Feb., about seven o'clock, I was standing at the door—I saw the prisoner and a man come up-I saw the man steal some chisel., and give some to the prisoner, who was alongside of him—I caught hold of the prisoner at the end of the stall—she got from me twice, but I caught her again—the man then came up, knocked me down, and said, "You b----, if you don't let her go I will kill you"—I got up and ran after her, down a court—the tools were <hi rend="italic">chuked</hi> away when I was knocked down—this chisel was found by a boy in the road—he gave it to the ploliceman.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. Were these things outside? Yes—Old-street is rather crowded sometimes—the man had some of the tools—the pri<lb></lb>soner had this one in her hand, and it dropped when I was knokced down.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-848" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-848" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-848" type="surname" value="BRANNAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-848" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES BRANNAN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-sergeant G</hi> 20.) I accompanied Penny to Wake<lb></lb>field-place, in Bunhill-row, and found the prisoner in a privy—this chisel was picked up in my presence by a child.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-849" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-849" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-849" type="surname" value="PENNY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-849" type="given" value="ALFRED"></interp>ALFRED PENNY</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I had never seen the prisoner before—I have not the least doubt of her being the person—she had got as far as Wakefield—place, which is two or three minutes walk from our shop.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
